      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Just for kicks, I recently put up a job post to find a writer/editor on Upwork.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "After getting about a dozen proposals, I quickly compiled a list of the first sentence of each one. (",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Click here",
          "marks": [
            "link-0"
          ]
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": " to see them all.)",
          "marks": []
        }
      ],
      "markDefs": [
        {
          "_key": "link-0",
          "_type": "link",
          "href": "https://docs.google.com/document/d/1GVcCZhMjjLiN5iJmHWs7WSGFYts_O2UD1J2V7AzrIb4/edit?usp=sharing"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Why?",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Well. If any writer is worth their salt, they’re going to write just as good a proposal as any form of content I could assign them.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Which means that, if I’m going to evaluate them on their writing ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "ability",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": " (which is what you ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "should do",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": " when hiring a writer), the best thing I can do is evaluate them based on how ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "well written",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": " their proposal is.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Assuming the Pareto Principle applies (which it most likely does), I could just as well take ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "any",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": " sentence from their proposal to gauge how well written their ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "entire piece",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": " might be.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "As long as I take the same sentence for each writer, and evaluate them based on that sentence alone, I have a pretty good method to use when comparing them.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "And it’s efficient too. ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Incredibly so",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": ". Because all I have to do is rank 12 sentences.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "…",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Lots of folks might argue that I need to read more from each writer to get a better impression of each. The thing is, not only does this take too long, it’s also not as effective. You can’t possibly compare a dozen 250, or 500, or 1,000 word pieces. In fact, this strategy is ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "more",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": " biased, because unless you have an abundantly clear winner (unless you find a ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "obvious choice",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": ") you’ll be so exhausted, you’ll likely pick the one you remember as being the best. (Causing you to rely on your somewhat spotty short-term memory.) It might be ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "better",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": " to pick a better sentence (say, the third or the last) or, even better, to identify the top 3 writers based on my ‘single sentence strategy,’ and then rank them based on their full piece. In either case, its a more effective (and certainly a more efficient) strategy than doing it the old-fashioned way.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Of course, if you’re merely looking for the cheapest writer you can afford, that’s another story.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}